&lt;p&gt;20 hours per week (5 x 4 hour shifts) 18.15-22.15&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic Staff Nurses to work as part of the Integrated Health and Social Care Team based within North Lincolnshire Community Services, based in one locality covering North Lincs.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Community Staff Nurses are an integral part of the District Nursing team providing skilled nursing care to patients in the community over a 24 hour period.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To assist with the assessment of care needs the development of care programmes and the implementation and evaluation of care. To carry out unsupervised delegated nursing duties, and to be an effective member of the network teams, developing and maintaining effective channels of communication with other professionals and agencies. Supervise and support unqualified staff, and act as mentor for pre-registration students.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You must be flexible, caring, and professional and have the ability to remain calm under pressure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These posts will cover the evening element of the service between 18.15- 22.15&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We expect you to provide advice and information to patients and their carers as appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
